enhanced_by.reason: The addComposited method initializes and modifies the composite array, which is directly used by the containsKey method to check for key presence.
The removeComposited method modifies the composite array, which affects the state of the map and thus the result of the containsKey method.
The put method adds a key-value pair to the map, which can affect the result of the containsKey method by potentially adding the key to be checked.
The remove method removes a key-value pair from the map, which can affect the result of the containsKey method by potentially removing the key to be checked.
